\end{align*}

To solve this system, we can multiply the first equation by $3$ and subtract it from the second equation to eliminate $y$:

\begin{align*}
(2x + 3y) - 3(3x + y) &= 220 - 3(155) \\
2x + 3y - 9x - 3y &= 220 - 465 \\
-7x &= -245 \\
x &= \frac{-245}{-7} = 35.
\end{align*}

Substituting this value of $x$ back into the first equation to solve for $y$:

\begin{align*}
3(35) + y &= 155 \\
105 + y &= 155 \\
y &= 155 - 105 = 50.
\end{align*}

